1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 ( { Black immediately fights for the centre, but allows White to push d5. If you don’t want to allow White the option of playing f2-f4 Benoni lines, } 2... e6 { is a move order you can try. After } 3. Nc3 { you can then go for the Nimzo-Indian instead, while after } ( 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 { you reach Benoni lines. Here } 4... d6 { is an important detail, taking away some of White’s dangerous options. After } 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 { followed by 8. Qxe4+. } ) ) 3. d5 e6 { Black is challenging White's centre. } 4. Nc3 exd5 { We're exchanging on d5 straight away. Otherwise White can play e4 and then retake on d5 with the e-pawn, resulting in a symmetrical position where Black is slightly worse because of his lack of space. } 5. cxd5 d6 { We prevent White's d5-d6 and prepare to fianchetto our dark-squared bishop with ...g6. This is the starting position of the Benoni. } 6. e4 { A natural and ambitious move. } 6... g6 { We continue the plan to fianchetto our bishop. } 7. h3 { White takes away the option of ...Bg4. } 7... Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. Be3 { This is a relatively new plan. White wants to develop the light square bishop to d3 next, considering that an immediate ...b5 is advantageous to him. That's because the e-file is now covered, and White can play Bxb5 directly without spending a tempo on Bd3. } 9... b5 { This is the most direct approach. We don't allow White to get his desired setup (with Bd3 and O-O, or Nd2 and Be2). It leads to unclear positions, somehow different from the typical Benoni ones. } 10. e5 { This is White's idea. By giving up the e-pawn he closes the diagonal of our dark-squared bishop and clears the path for the d-pawn. White will regain a pawn on the next move. } 10... dxe5 { We have to take this pawn, there is not much of a choice. } 11. Bxb5 e4 ( { An important move. } 11... Nbd7 { has been played so far, but it gives White easy play and an advantage. We need to open up the Bg7 right away. } ) 12. Ne5 { The only real test. } 12... Nh5 { We need to attack the e5-knight and see where it goes. } *

