1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 ( { Black immediately fights for the centre, but allows White to push d5. If you don’t want to allow White the option of playing f2-f4 Benoni lines, } 2... e6 { is a move order you can try. After } 3. Nc3 { you can then go for the Nimzo-Indian instead, while after } ( 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 { you reach Benoni lines. Here } 4... d6 { is an important detail, taking away some of White’s dangerous options. After } 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 { followed by 8. Qxe4+. } ) ) 3. d5 e6 { Black is challenging White's centre. } 4. Nc3 exd5 { We're exchanging on d5 straight away. Otherwise White can play e4 and then retake on d5 with the e-pawn, resulting in a symmetrical position where Black is slightly worse because of his lack of space. } 5. cxd5 d6 { We prevent White's d5-d6 and prepare to fianchetto our dark-squared bishop with ...g6. This is the starting position of the Benoni. } 6. e4 { A natural and ambitious move. } 6... g6 { We continue the plan to fianchetto our bishop. } 7. Nge2 { White will bring the knight to g3 where it defends the e4 pawn. In case of ...h5 ideas he will play Bg5. Besides, he's trying to save time on the f2-f3 move; he may play f2-f4 in one move. } 7... h5 { Preventing Ng3 so that White doesn't have time to develop his pieces to their desired positions. } 8. Bg5 { White takes advantage of the g5-square. } 8... Bg7 9. Qd2 { It's natural to develop the queen to d2. However, this takes away White's option to play Nc1-b3-d2. } 9... a6 { It makes sense to delay ...O-O for the time being, so that White cannot play Ng3. } ( { I tried to make the variations with } 9... O-O 10. Ng3 h4 { work, but White is slightly better after } 11. e5 ) 10. a4 Nbd7 { This move was part of our plan anyway. } 11. Nc1 Qc7 { The queen is useful here, and we can consider ...c4 later on. } 12. Be2 { White has managed to skip the move f2-f3 for now. } 12... Rb8 { This is useful, as we prepare ...c4 followed by ...b5. We're still flexible about castling. } 13. O-O c4 { We can start our queenside counterplay immediately. } *

