1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 { White is eager to get to the London System setup as soon as possible. } 2... d5 { This is good since White has showed his intentions so early. } 3. e3 e6 ( { We just transpose to our setup against the London. } 3... c5 { is also good, but then we need to consider the lines with } 4. dxc5 { as well. } ) 4. Nd2 c5 { Fighting for the centre. } 5. c3 Nc6 { The knight is well placed here. } 6. Bg3 { This is a useful waiting move. White is trying to be tricky. } 6... Be7 { Since ...Nh5 is not available for now, we can just complete our development instead. } 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Ngf3 { Sooner or later White had to play this move. } 8... Nh5 { Now that it’s allowed we go for the dark-squared bishop. } 9. Ne5 g6 { Defending the knight and keeping the status quo on the kingside. } *

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Modern Benoni"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter: White Avoids the Benoni"]
[Black "3. g3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 { White delays c4 for now and first wants to fianchetto the bishop to g2 and castle. } 3... c5 { The typical break in the spirit of the Benoni. } 4. Bg2 cxd4 { If allowed we will take the pawn on d4. } 5. Nxd4 { Sooner or later White has to take the pawn back. } 5... d5 6. O-O e5 { We use this opportunity to drive the knight away, while getting new perspectives for our light-squared bishop. } 7. Nb3 { A natural retreat. } 7... Be6 { The bishop belongs here in order to defend the centre. } 8. Nc3 { White’s most common move. } 8... Be7 9. Bg5 { Indirectly attacking the d5-pawn. } 9... Nbd7 { This is an important nuance. The d5-pawn is now defended. } 10. f4 { White claims this break works better with the knight on d7. I'm not convinced though. } 10... exf4 ( { The obvious reply. There is no need for a fancy move like } 10... d4 { . } ) 11. Bxf4 { White could have gotten this with the knight on b8. While it would be nice to be able to develop this knight to c6, we are a tempo up nevertheless. } 11... Qb6+ { It's worth including this check. } 12. Kh1 O-O { Black has finished his development and has good chances in the resulting middlegame. } *

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Modern Benoni"]
