e on Black! } 13... Nb6 ( { Normally I'd like to have the knight closer to our king. However, in this case White is slow with his attack and the knight helps us to get a dynamic position. After } 13... Bb7 14. Be3 Nf6 15. Re1 Nbd7 16. Bf2 { White gets a grip on the position. } ) 14. f5 N8d7 { We need this knight in the defence. } 15. Bg5 Bf6 16. h4 { Usually White wants to play this in one move. Here he has lost time by first playing h3. } 16... Bxg5 17. hxg5 b4 { We are just in time with our counterplay. } 18. axb4 cxb4 19. Ne2 Nc5 { The knight has a nice outpost on c5. } 20. Ned4 Nbd7 { It's not easy for White to continue his attack. } *

