he rook. } ) 14... Nf6 ( { This is normal, as we want to bring the rook to e7. } 14... f5 15. Ng5 Nf8 { is possible as well. } ) 15. Qh4 Ng4 { A queen exchange is good for us because it means White won't have any attack, while we'll be able to push on the queenside. } 16. Qg3 Rae7 { On e7 the rook can come under attack after f5 followed by Bg5, but we'll gladly sacrifice an exchange for the initiative! } 17. f5 Ne5 18. Bc2 Nbd7 { Black is fine with so many pieces amassed in the centre. } *

