e rook. } ) 14... Ne5 { We need to exchange the f3-knight in order to gain access to the e5-square and reduce White's attacking possibilities. } 15. Bg5 Bf6 { A suitable reply, preventing White’s intended f6. } 16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. Nxe5 Qxe5 { The dark squares around our king are weakened, so we need to bring up the knight to cover those squares up. } 18. Qd2 Nd7 19. Rf3 Qe7 { The knight on e5 will compensate for the slightly weakened king’s position. } *

