ght so as not to be material down. } 22. axb6 dxc3 23. bxc3 Nd3 { Only going forward, even at the cost of the e4-pawn. We cannot allow White to enjoy his pair of bishops. } 24. Bxd3 exd3 25. Rd1 { The most natural move. White wants to take the dangerous d3-pawn as soon as possible. } 25... Bd7 { The bishop feels good here as it blocks the d6-pawn. } 26. Rxd3 Rfe8 { Black is a pawn down, but his position is a tough nut to crack. } *

