 e5 { Black needs to develop the knight to c7 via a6. } ) ( 12... Re8 { is a useful move, but afterwards Black still needs to go ... Na6. That's why I prefer to play ...Na6 directly and try to bring the knight to c7 faster. } ) 13. e5 { This doesn't pose Black any serious problems. } 13... dxe5 ( { I prefer to take this pawn, although } 13... Nc7 { is possible as well. } ) 14. f5 e4 { I think this is the easiest. We give the pawn back but open up our bishop. } 15. Nxe4 Nf6 { We need to get rid of the e4-knight. } 16. Nxf6+ Qxf6 17. Bg5 Qxf5 18. Be7 Bd7 ( { There is nothing wrong with } 18... Re8 { , but I like the idea of offering an exchange sacrifice. After } ) ( 18... Bd7 19. Bxf8 Rxf8 { Black's active pieces compensate for the exchange. } ) *

