s development. } 13... a6 { is also possible, but probably it will just transpose back to 13... Nbd7. } ) 14. Be3 { The bishop prevents any checks on the g1-a7 diagonal and later on could go to h4 via f2. } 14... a6 { Now its a good moment to include this move. } 15. a4 Qa5 { The idea is to play ...Qb4 threatening both ...c4 and the b2-pawn. Also it comes in handy to bring either rook to e8. } 16. Bf2 Rae8 { Our king’s rook is useful on f8 because in some lines we have ...Nh5 followed by ...f5. We're preparing ...Qb4 or even ...c4 directly. } ( { The immediate } 16... Qb4 { is also possible, and then } 17. a5 Nh5 { with the idea ...f5 is interesting. } ) 17. Kh1 Qb4 { Just according to our plan. } 18. Rfb1 { White intends to trap our queen after 19. a5. } 18... c4 19. Bc2 Qa5 { Mission accomplished: we have achieved ...c4, so now the queen moves back to prevent White from playing a5. ...Nc5 is up next. } *

