1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Nf3 a6 { I recommend this move as White cannot parry both ...b5 and ...Bg4. Thus we manage to solve some of Black’s strategical problems in the position. } 8. Bf4 b5 { This transposes to the chapter 6. Nf3 g6 7. Bf4. } *

