1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Nf3 a6 { I recommend this move as White cannot parry both ...b5 and ...Bg4. Thus we manage to solve some of Black’s strategical problems in the position. } 8. h3 { I think this is a strong move. White prevents ...Bg4 once and for all and is going to get a nice setup with Bd3 and Bf4, putting pressure on the d6-pawn. } 8... b5 { Otherwise we would allow White to play a4 and Bd3. } 9. Bd3 Bg7 10. O-O O-O 11. Bf4 ( { White doesn't make it easy for us to play ...Nbd7. } 11. Re1 { may well transpose after } 11... Nbd7 12. Bf4 Qe7 ( 12... Qb6 { . } ) 13. Qd2 { , although in this line we have the extra option of } ) 11... Qe7 ( { I’ve analyzed this position for a long time. Finally I came to like the idea to develop the knight to d7 quickly. } 11... Qb6 { with the same idea would be wrong because of } 12. a4 b4 13. a5 { with a big advantage, } ) ( { while after } 11... Re8 12. Re1 Ra7 13. a3 Rae7 14. Rc1 Qb6 15. b4 Nbd7 16. Be3 { White keeps some pressure. } ) 12. Qd2 { This is more flexible since White doesn't show yet where he intends to put his rooks. } 12... Nbd7 13. Rae1 { A refined move, with the idea to push f4 after exchanges on e5. Otherwise White can undermine the queenside pawn chain with b3 and a4. } 13... Ne5 { It's best to go for this anyway, as I don't see any other useful moves to improve the position. } 14. Nxe5 dxe5 15. Be3 c4 { Otherwise White plays b3 and then attacks our c5-pawn. } 16. Bc2 Ne8 ( { This move demands to be played! The knight will occupy a nice square on d6. } 16... Bd7 17. f4 b4 18. Ne2 exf4 19. Bd4 { looks preferable for White. } ) 17. f4 Nd6 ( { White can pin the knight with Bc5 but this doesn't do much because there is no way to put any further pressure on the knight. If } 17... exf4 18. Bxf4 Be5 19. Bxe5 Qxe5 20. Ne2 { and White’s central pawns will push forward - there is no blockade. } ) 18. f5 Bd7 { With an unclear position. White will push on the kingside, while Black will play ...b4 and ...a5 on the other flank. } *

