1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Nf3 a6 { I recommend this move as White cannot parry both ...b5 and ...Bg4. Thus we manage to solve some of Black’s strategical problems in the position. } 8. Be2 { This is a tricky move. White is going for quick development, and we need to be careful about the possibility of e4-e5. } 8... Bg7 ( { We need to continue developing, as otherwise White's e5-push will be strong. For example, } 8... Bg4 { is wrong because of } 9. e5 { White gets a strong initiative. } ) 9. O-O O-O ( { We have two ideas here: ...Bg4 and ...b5. White cannot stop them both at the same time. The immediate } 9... Bg4 { is also possible. } ) 10. e5 { This is not dangerous now. } 10... dxe5 11. Nxe5 Nbd7 { The d5-pawn may prove to be a weakness instead of a strength. } *

