1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Nf3 a6 { I recommend this move as White cannot parry both ...b5 and ...Bg4. Thus we manage to solve some of Black’s strategical problems in the position. } 8. Be2 { This is a tricky move. White is going for quick development, and we need to be careful about the possibility of e4-e5. } 8... Bg7 ( { We need to continue developing, as otherwise White's e5-push will be strong. For example, } 8... Bg4 { is wrong because of } 9. e5 { White gets a strong initiative. } ) 9. a4 { White prevents ...b5 and prepares Nd2. } 9... Bg4 ( 9... O-O { is not bad, but after } 10. Nd2 { we would get into a different line than the one I covered against this setup, so this is not covered in this repertoire. } ) 10. Nd2 { Otherwise we can exchange the knight on f3. } 10... Bxe2 11. Qxe2 O-O 12. Nc4 { This is the point: White delays castling in order to attack the d6-pawn with Bf4. } 12... Nbd7 ( { We have to go for this pawn sacrifice. The backwards move } 12... Ne8 { is not recommended because after } 13. Bf4 Nd7 14. O-O { White gets a long-lasting hold on the position. } ) 13. Nxd6 { the real test of this variation. } 13... Ne5 { Now there follows a forced sequence. } 14. Nc4 Nxc4 15. Qxc4 Qa5 { We prepare ...b5. } 16. O-O b5 { We open up the position by means of a second pawn sacrifice. } 17. Qxc5 Rfc8 { We need to move this rook (and not the one on a8) in order to keep the a6-pawn defended. } 18. Qe3 Re8 { Attacking both the e4- and d5- pawns. } 19. f3 b4 { We regain the pawn on d5 with good compensation for the other sacrificed pawn. } 20. Nd1 { White plans to bring the knight to f2 or e3. } 20... Nxd5 { We regain a pawn with tempo. } 21. Qb3 Qc5+ { It's good to include this check. } 22. Kh1 Nb6 { With the strong threat of ...Qc4. } 23. Bd2 Qc4 { White’s extra pawn will not really be felt in the resulting ending. } 24. Qxc4 Nxc4 25. Bxb4 Rab8 26. Bc3 Nxb2 { With a drawish ending because of our active pieces. We still have to play carefully though because White is a pawn up. } *

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Modern Benoni"]
