[Black "8. a4 Bg7 9. h3 with 10. e3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. Bf4 a6 ( { Black prevents the early check with Qa4+. This is a more solid and less forcing line. The alternative } 7... Bg7 { which is covered in the next chapter, leads to very double-edged play because Black often sacrifices a pawn for quick development. } ) 8. a4 { White prevents ...b5 and later on they can play a5 in order to make use of the b6-square. The variation 8. e4 b5 was covered in the previous chapter. } 8... Bg7 9. h3 { Both preventing ...Bg4 and creating a refuge for the bishop on h2. } 9... O-O 10. e3 { This is the point. On e4 the pawn would have been a target. By playing e3, White can first finish their development and only then prepare the advance of the e-pawn. } 10... Ne8 { In this position Black has tried many different plans. With 10... Ne8 we defend the d6-pawn and prepare ...Nd7. Also in some lines, because the d6-pawn is protected, we can forego having to play ...Qe7. } ( { If Black plays } 10... b6 { immediately then White can reply } 11. Nd2 Ne8 12. Nc4 { with pressure on d6. } ) 11. a5 { This is quite a rare move. Most players will complete their development first. White considers that he has to play this anyway. The idea is that after ...Nd7 and ...Ne5, after an exchange on e5, if we take back with the d6-pawn our c5-pawn will remain weak. However, that’s quite far into the future and we don’t have to follow that exact plan. } 11... Nd7 { In this case we're going to open up the position on the queenside with ...Rb8 and ...b5. } 12. Be2 Rb8 { We're going for this because we intend to take back on b6 with the rook. } 13. Nd2 { White intends to bring the knight to c4. } 13... b5 { Continuing with our plan. } 14. axb6 Rxb6 { This is slightly more ambitious than taking with the knight. Now the rook will go to b4. } 15. Nc4 { This misses a simple tactic. } 15... Rxb2 { White loses an important pawn. } 16. Nxb2 { Recapturing like this is not possible, as } 16... Bxc3+ { wins. } *

