y to find, as White has many choices. Now the knight is ready to jump to a5. } 17... Nc7 { Trying to slowly bring the pieces into play. } 18. Na5 Bd7 { It is crucial that we keep an eye on the c6-square! Black’s position is playable. We can continue with ...f5, ...Rfb8 or ...Nb5 depending on White's reply. } *

