1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. e4 Bg7 8. Be2 Bg4 ( { If possible we should take advantage of this move order. I like to exchange our light-squared bishop on f3. } 8... O-O { is also good. } ) 9. Bf4 O-O { We can continue developing. } 10. O-O a6 { Although it could be delayed, this is a good moment to include ...a6. } 11. a4 Qe7 { Preparing ...Nbd7. } 12. Qc2 Nbd7 13. Rfe1 Rab8 { Preparing to play ...b5. } 14. a5 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Ne8 { A typical maneuver. The knight is heading to c7 after which we are ready to play ...b5. } 16. Be2 { The bishop is better positioned on the f1-a8 diagonal. } 16... Nc7 17. Bd2 b5 18. axb6 Rxb6 { Black has a good position, although he lost in 1-0 (46) Inarkiev,E (2667)-Lupulescu,C  (2598) Rijeka 2010. } *

