} 16... Qa5 { Planning to continue with ...Ba4. } 17. O-O Ba4 { Again, making room for the knight to go to d7 with tempo. } 18. Bc2 Bxc2 ( { The easy solution. There is no need for } 18... cxb2 { . } ) 19. Qxc2 Nbd7 { We develop the knight with tempo. } 20. Bd4 Nxd5 { Time to take back the pawn! } 21. Nxd5 Qxd5 22. Rfd1 Bxd4 { This exchange would happen sooner or later. } 23. Rxd4 Qb5 { With an equal position, as played in a correspondence game. It's not easy for White to take the c3-pawn. } *

