rong now. In any case our c-pawn couldn't be defended. } 17. bxc3 Bxf1 { Thus White loses the right to castle. } 18. Kxf1 Nbd7 ( { We attack the bishop while developing. } 18... Qa6+ { is also possible. } ) 19. Bxf6 Nxf6 20. c4 { White tries to maintain his central pawns. } 20... Qa6 { With a double attack: both ...Nxd5 and ...Qxa2 are threatened. } 21. Kg1 Qxa2 { With good compensation for the pawn. We can play ...Nd7 and then push our passed pawns. } *

