sition and gaining time to take the d5-pawn. } 17. Rxa3 Bf8 ( 17... Nbd7 { is also possible, but the bishop move is slightly more precise. } ) 18. d6 Nbd7 { Everything comes with gain of tempo. } 19. Bd4 Qxd6 { This is the main idea behind playing ...Bf8 first instead of ...Nbd7, although Black's position is playable in any case. } 20. Be2 Nd5 { With an unclear position. We are not material down and the c4-pawn is well-protected. The correspondence game ½-½ (30) Bolz, B (2384)-Dimov, D (2432) ICCF 2017 continued } 21. O-O a6 22. Ra1 Nb4 { and Black was doing fine. In time Black can prepare a knight jump to d3. } *

