here it goes to b5 next. } 16. Nc4 Bb5 17. Bg5 h6 { It's good to clarify where the bishop goes. If White retreats it to f4 it's similar to the immediate 17. Bf4, while if it moves to h4 we can take it after ...g5, ...Bxc4 and ...Nh5. Black has a normal Benoni position. } *

