repertoire for Chessable. The idea is simple: White is preparing b4, in order to open up the position on the queenside in a favourable way. } 14... Bxc4 ( { We exchange right away in order to play ...a6 and prepare ...b5. } 14... Qd7 { is also interesting, but it isn't clear to me that the queen is needed on d7 in all the lines. Sometimes ...Nd7 is a more useful move. } ) 15. Bxc4 a6 { The first step in preparing ...b5. Afterwards we can continue with either ...Nd7 or ...Qd7. } 16. b4 { White carries out their main plan as well. } 16... Nd7 { A typical move. We're ready to take back on c5 with the knight. } 17. bxc5 Nxc5 { The knight is well placed on c5, and we can play ...Rb8 to prepare ...b5. } ( { Of course, } 17... Bxc3 { would have been wrong because of } 18. cxb6 { after which the knight on c7 has nowhere to go. } ) *

