on. } 15. b3 { White wants to take with the pawn on c4. On the other hand the c3-knight is undefended for the moment. } 15... Bxc4 { Sooner or later we have to go for this move. } 16. bxc4 Ng4 17. Qe1 ( { Defending both c3 and f2. } 17. fxg4 Bxc3 { would provide Black good control over the e5-square. } ) 17... Bd4+ 18. Kh1 Ne3 { We force White to give up their dark-squared bishop. } 19. Bxe3 Bxe3 20. Bd3 Bd4 { With a playable position. Black can seek counterplay with ...f5. } *

