! } 18. Qxd3 Bd4+ { This check allows us to take the d6-knight on  the next move. } 19. Kh1 Qxd6 { The pin on the b5-knight makes this possible. } 20. Nxd6 Bxd3 21. Nxe8 Nc6 { It's good for Black to keep one pair of rooks on the board, and this way we finish our development. } 22. Nf6+ Kg7 23. Rd1 c4 { Firmly keeping the bishops in the centre. } 24. Nd5 Rb8 { Black has good compensation for the sacrificed pawn  because of his very active pieces. White also faces significant problems developing the queenside pieces. } *

