 of playing ...Bb5. } 19. Qa3 { White prevents ...Bb5. } 19... Be8 { Preparing ...Nd7. } 20. Nd2 Nd7 { The knight is heading to e5. } 21. Bxd6 Ne5 ( { We go for some tactical tricks. } 21... Nf6 { is also good. } ) 22. Bxc5 Nxd3 23. Qxd3 Bc6 { Very strong. A timely return into play for the bishop. } 24. d6 Qg5 { It all works out for Black. } 25. Ne4 Qf5 { White will have to give the pawn back to disentangle his pieces. For example } 26. Re1 ( { Alternatively, } 26. d7 Qxd7 27. Qxd7 Bxd7 { leaves us with the pair of bishops. } ) 26... Re8 { and after ...h5 in order to secure the last rank, we threaten to take the knight. } *

