 a forced move. Now we’ve managed to untangle our pieces and the d5-pawn is still hanging. } 21. Nc4 Bxd5 { We take the pawn and activate our bishop. } 22. Nexd6 Nb6 { Going for some exchanges. } 23. Nxb6 Qxd6 { Forcing even more exchanges. It was possible to take the other knight as well. } 24. Nxd5 Qxd5 { And here after } 25. Qf4 Qxd3 26. Bxf6 Qb1+ 27. Kh2 Qxa2 { the correspondence game ½-½ (30) Mostowik,D (2266)-Legemaat,G (2382) ICCF 2015 soon ended in a draw. } *

