1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 ( 6. Nf3 g6 7. h3 Bg7 8. e4 O-O { is another way to reach the mainline of this chapter. } ) 6... g6 7. h3 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. Be3 { This is a relatively new plan. White wants to develop the light-squared bishop to d3 next, considering that an immediate ...b5 is advantageous to him. That's because the e-file is now covered, and White can play Bxb5 directly, without spending time on Bd3. } 9... b5 { However, this is still the most direct approach. We don't allow White to get his desired setup (with Bd3 and O-O, or Nd2 and Be2). This move leads to unclear positions, somehow different from the typical Benoni ones. } 10. e5 { This is White's idea. By giving up the e-pawn he closes the diagonal of our dark-squared bishop and clears the path for the d-pawn. White will win back a pawn on the next move. } 10... dxe5 { We have to take the pawn; there is not much of a choice. } 11. Bxb5 e4 ( { An important move. } 11... Nbd7 { has been played in earlier games, but it gives White easy play and an advantage. We need to open up the diagonal of the g7-bishop right away. } ) 12. Ne5 { The only real test. } 12... Nh5 { We need to challenge the e5-knight and see where it goes. } 13. Nc6 { White is acting quickly and goes forward with his pieces. } 13... Nxc6 { We gladly exchange our undeveloped knight for White's strong knight. } 14. Bxc6 Ba6 { This is a typical exchange sacrifice in this variation. It is important not to allow White to castle. } 15. Qa4 { White attacks both the a6-bishop and the e4-pawn. } 15... Bxc3+ { The most direct response. With energetic moves we have to play against the white king stuck in the centre. } 16. bxc3 Qf6 { Eyeing the c3-pawn and preparing a future ...Nf4. } 17. Rc1 Bd3 { Now the direct threat is ...Nf4. } 18. Bxa8 Nf4 ( { There is no time to retake on a8 as after } 18... Rxa8 { White could play } 19. Qc6 { . } ) 19. Bxf4 Qxf4 { The main factor in this position is White’s weak king. } 20. Rd1 { Threatening Rxd3. } 20... Qg5 { We need to remove our  queen from the pin on the 4th rank. } 21. Rxd3 { This is White's ticket to castle. } 21... exd3 22. O-O Rxa8 { With an equal endgame. } *

