1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 ( 6. Nf3 g6 7. h3 Bg7 8. e4 O-O { is another way to reach the mainline of this chapter. } ) 6... g6 7. h3 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. Be3 { This is a relatively new plan. White wants to develop the light-squared bishop to d3 next, considering that an immediate ...b5 is advantageous to him. That's because the e-file is now covered, and White can play Bxb5 directly, without spending time on Bd3. } 9... b5 { However, this is still the most direct approach. We don't allow White to get his desired setup (with Bd3 and O-O, or Nd2 and Be2). This move leads to unclear positions, somehow different from the typical Benoni ones. } 10. e5 { This is White's idea. By giving up the e-pawn he closes the diagonal of our dark-squared bishop and clears the path for the d-pawn. White will win back a pawn on the next move. } 10... dxe5 { We have to take the pawn; there is not much of a choice. } 11. Bxb5 e4 ( { An important move. } 11... Nbd7 { has been played in earlier games, but it gives White easy play and an advantage. We need to open up the diagonal of the g7-bishop right away. } ) 12. Ne5 { The only real test. } 12... Nh5 { We need to challenge the e5-knight and see where it goes. } 13. Nc6 { White is acting quickly and goes forward with his pieces. } 13... Nxc6 { We gladly exchange our undeveloped knight for White's strong knight. } 14. dxc6 { White is advancing his passed pawn. } 14... Qa5 { The queen is more actively placed here than on b6. } 15. Be2 { This is slow. } 15... Ba6 { Black has other possibilities as well, but this is more forcing. } 16. O-O Bxc3 { For Benoni players it's hard to give up this bishop, but sometimes it can be done. The c3-knight was controlling important squares like e4 and d5. } 17. bxc3 Rfd8 { This comes with tempo. It's better to play the f8-rook so that later White won’t be able to play Bh6 with gain of tempo. } 18. Qe1 Bd3 { Now if White takes the bishop we take back with the e-pawn. } 19. Bg5 Rd6 { Black has good play. The c6-pawn is about to fall. } *

