ove the rook from f8 - we need to get the attack going quickly. } 18. Bxf8 { This is a bad moment for White to take the rook. } 18... Bxh3 { Now White is losing. } 19. g4 f3 ( { The white king is left without defense. Be careful not to play } 19... Bxg4 { because of } 20. Be7 { and White wins. } ) 20. Ne3 Nf4 { White gets checkmated or suffers big material losses. } *

