4. h4 g4 15. Nh2 Kh7 16. Nf1 Ne5 { Black's moves are very natural, just developing and centralizing the pieces. } 17. Ne3 { White is eager to bring the knight into play, but this move limits the d2-bishop's activity. } 17... Bg6 18. b3 { 0-1 (58) Jakovenko,D (2704)-Pantsulaia,L (2607) Doha rapid 2016. } 18... Nh5 { With the idea ...f5. Black is already better. White's pieces are misplaced, and we can push on both flanks: ...f5 on the kingside, or we can prepare ...b5 on the other flank. } *

