-e3 or Nd3-f4. } 14... Kh7 ( { In this position this is preferable to } 14... h5 { , as we don't weaken the position too much. } ) 15. Nc2 Bg6 ( { This is slightly more precise, as the direct } 15... Nbd7 { may allow } 16. Bf4 { . } ) 16. Ne3 Nbd7 17. a4 Ne5 { We can slowly prepare the ...b5 push on the queenside by ...b6, ...a6, ...Rb8 and ...Qd7. White is lacking a clear plan. Black is doing fine. } *

