-e3 or Nd3-f4. } 14... Kh7 ( { In this position this is preferable to } 14... h5 { , as we don't weaken the position too much. } ) 15. Nc2 Bg6 ( { This is slightly more precise, as the direct } 15... Nbd7 { may allow } 16. Bf4 { . } ) 16. Ne3 Nbd7 17. h5 { White exchanges their h-pawn for our g-pawn. } 17... Nxh5 18. Nxg4 f5 { A tempting move. We're going for an attack on White’s king. } 19. Nxh6 f4 { This is the most direct move. } 20. Ng4 Ne5 { It makes sense to exchange White's active knight. } 21. Nxe5 Bxe5 22. gxf4 Bf6 { The most precise. } 23. e4 Rg8 { The white king is in grave danger. } *

