1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. f3 { . } 7... Bg7 8. Bg5 h6 { It makes sense to include this in order to remove the bishop from its active position. } 9. Be3 a6 { Sooner or later we have to go for this move. } 10. a4 O-O ( 10... Nbd7 { would be imprecise because it allows White to set up with } 11. Nh3 { followed by Nf2. } ) 11. Qd2 Re8 12. Bd3 ( { The h6-pawn is taboo. If } 12. Bxh6 { there is } 12... Nxe4 ) 12... h5 { The h6-pawn was not hanging, but I think ...h5 is a useful move in any case. } 13. Nge2 Nbd7 { Followed by ...Ne5 with a good position for Black. Most likely we'll try to play on the queenside with ...Rb8, ...Bd7 and ...b5. We can exchange the e5-knight for the bishop at the right moment. White can consider the plan with Rb1 and b4. An interesting fight lies ahead. } *

