1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Bg5 Bg7 8. Nf3 { White wants to get an improved version of the Nf3-d2 variation by developing the dark-squared bishop first. We have to use the fact that White saved on the move h3 and try to exchange our light-squared bishop. } 8... a6 ( { First we have to secure the a4-e8 diagonal, preparing both ...b5 and ...Bg4. A hasty } 8... O-O { would allow White to play } 9. Nd2 { and get a firm hold on the position. } ) 9. Nd2 { White avoids ...Bg4 but allows ...b5. } 9... h6 ( { It may be a good idea to include ...h6 in this line. Of course there is nothing wrong with } 9... O-O { either. } ) 10. Bh4 b5 { Now we go for this, as otherwise White can prevent ...b5 with a4. } 11. Be2 O-O 12. Qc2 Re8 { We are only making natural moves. } 13. O-O Nbd7 { Black has managed to play ...b5 and is ready for the fight ahead. } *

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Modern Benoni"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
