1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Bd3 Bg7 8. Bg5 O-O 9. Qd2 { White delays the development of the knight on g1, keeping options open to either develop it to f3 or e2. White also prevents ...h6 and reinforces the e1-a5 diagonal so that an early ...b5 doesn't work. However, the drawback is obvious: White's play is slow and thus their king is still in the centre. } 9... a6 { Since immediate ...b5 ideas are not possible anymore, it seems good to include ...a6 and a4. } 10. a4 Re8 { The rook is useful on the e-file. } 11. Nf3 Bg4 { This is good for Black. } *

