1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Bd3 Bg7 8. Bg5 O-O 9. Nge2 h6 { While other moves are possible as well, I think it's good to check what White is going to do with his bishop. } 10. Bf4 ( { This only helps us to activate our pieces. } 10. Be3 Ng4 { is also in our favour. } ) 10... Nh5 11. Be3 Nd7 { The knight will come to e5 on the next move. } *

