1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Be2 Bg7 8. Nf3 Bg4 { Given the opportunity we can exchange our light-squared bishop for a knight, or even a bishop. } 9. Nd2 { White relocates the knight to c4. } 9... Bxe2 10. Qxe2 O-O 11. Nc4 Nbd7 { We're just in time to fight against the white knight on c4. The same position with the moves ...a6 and a4 included was treated in another chapter, but this is a more favourable version for us. } 12. O-O Nb6 { We won't let the c4-knight stay for too long! } 13. Ne3 Qe7 { With a balanced position. The trade of bishops has helped us solve the issues with our lack of space. A good plan for Black is to put a rook on e8, play ...Nh5 and go for ...f5. } *

