1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 c5 4. g3 { White avoids the Benoni and goes for an English Opening setup. They want to develop with Bg2, putting pressure on the long diagonal. } 4... cxd4 { We have to act fast before White has time to comfortably establish their ideal setup. } 5. Nxd4 d5 { with a long-lasting initiative in return for the pawn. } 6. Bg2 ( { I like this natural move. We simply fight for the centre. Of course } 6. cxd5 { is not good because we can take back with the queen } 6... Qxd5 { . } ) 6... e5 { This is a good moment to push the pawns in the centre. This allows us to gain space and we'll be able to develop our pieces to good squares. } 7. Nc2 { This looks like a strange place to put the knight. } 7... d4 { We keep the centre intact. } 8. O-O Nc6 9. b4 { White ignores the centre for now and goes for counterplay on the queenside. } 9... Be7 { We ignore White's threats. if } 10. b5 { we can answer } 10... Na5 { . The nice centre gives Black a good position. } *

