1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 { White delays c4 for now and first wants to fianchetto the bishop to g2 and castle. } 3... c5 ( { The typical break in the spirit of the Benoni. Of course, Black has other good alternatives like } 3... d5 { transposing to the Catalan, or } ) ( 3... b5 { which is another way to exploit the fact that White has delayed playing c4. } ) 4. c3 { Just supporting the centre. This is solid but passive. } 4... Nc6 { There is a rule in chess saying that we should develop the knights first, so let's follow it! } 5. Bg2 d5 { The position resembles a fianchetto Slav with reversed colours. } 6. O-O Be7 7. Nbd2 O-O { Black doesn't have any problems. We may consider ...a5 in order to gain some space on the queenside, since White cannot make use of the b5-square. } *

