 has } 14. Qxd5 Bxh4 15. Qe4 { , winning. } ) 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. cxd5 Nb4 ( { This is an attempt to liven up the position. } 13... exd5 { would be quite dull. } ) 14. dxe6 Bxf3 { Forcibly giving White doubled pawns. } 15. gxf3 Nxc2 16. Qxc2 Qxd4 { All the other captures are good as well. } 17. Rad1 { Until here we’ve been following the game ½-½ (27) Carlsen,M  (2765)-Leko,P (2741) Miskolc rapid 2008. } 17... Qc4 ( { With an equal position. White's pawn up doesn't really matter. Leko played } 17... Qh4 { and comfortably drew as well. } ) *

