1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 { White is eager to establish the London System setup as soon as possible. } 2... d5 { This is good since White has showed his intentions so early by immediately moving the bishop. } 3. e3 e6 ( { This way we just transpose to our setup against 2. Nf3 and 3. Bf4. } 3... c5 { is also fine, but in that case we need to consider the lines with } 4. dxc5 { as well. Now after 3... e6, if at any point White plays Nf3 a direct transposition to the lines after 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bf4 should occur. Of course, White has some independent tries as well. } ) 4. Nd2 c5 { Fighting for the centre. } 5. c3 Nc6 { Our knight is well placed on c6. } 6. Bg3 { This is a useful waiting move. White is trying to be tricky. } 6... Be7 { Since ...Nh5 is not available for now, we can just complete our development instead. } 7. Bd3 O-O 8. a3 g6 { And ...Nh5 is on the agenda again. } *

