tiative themselves, and this position is not in that spirit. } ) ) 10. f4 { Very logical. White supports the knight in the centre, hoping for a long-term edge. } 10... Qb6 { This is a big improvement over the above-mentioned game Lupulescu- Tabatabaei, Rasht 2017. This move actually introduces a double attack: both ...Qxb2 and ... Bxe5 are in the air (it seems better to go ...Bxe5 than ...Nxe5) as the e3-bishop is unprotected. } 11. Qb3 { The only way to stop both threats. } 11... Ng8 ( { A nice rejoinder. We want to go ...Nge7/...Nh6 followed by ...f6 in order to kick the e5-knight away from the centre. Exchanging the queens with } 11... Qxb3 { would give White a more comfortable ending. } ) 12. Qxb6 axb6 { If White is the one who exchanges queens this gives us a comfortable position, as White cannot attack the b6-pawn. } *

