1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 { The Colle System. White is building up the position slowly, and is going for a setup with Bd3, b3 and Bb2. This system is popular in blitz and rapid even among top players. Although it's not so ambitious, White develops all the pieces to good squares and gets a playable position. } 3... d5 ( { As much as I prefer to avoid symmetry, this seems more natural to me than } 3... c5 { . } ) 4. Bd3 c5 ( { We can fight for the centre straight away. A good alternative is } 4... Bd6 { , but that is too symmetrical for me! } ) 5. c4 { Doesn't pose any problems to Black. } 5... dxc4 { Gaining a tempo, as White has played Bd3 and then Bxc4. } 6. Bxc4 a6 { Black is doing fine. It's a Queen's Gambit Accepted type of position, similar to those in the previous chapter, where White has lost a tempo. } *

