1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 { The Colle System. White is building up the position slowly, and is going for a setup with Bd3, b3 and Bb2. This system is popular in blitz and rapid even among top players. Although it's not so ambitious, White develops all the pieces to good squares and gets a playable position. } 3... d5 ( { As much as I prefer to avoid symmetry, this seems more natural to me than } 3... c5 { . } ) 4. Bd3 c5 ( { We can fight for the centre straight away. A good alternative is } 4... Bd6 { , but that is too symmetrical for me! } ) 5. c3 { White prevents ...c4 and is going for a Meran-like setup with reversed colours. } 5... b6 { It's a good idea for us to develop the light-squared bishop as soon as possible. } 6. Nbd2 Bb7 7. O-O Be7 { Preparing to castle. For the moment we remain flexible about where to develop the b8-knight. } 8. Qe2 O-O { This is flexible. } 9. Ne5 Nbd7 10. f4 Rc8 ( { This move can be useful in the long-term. } 10... Ne8 { or } ) ( 10... Ne4 { are also playable. } ) 11. b3 Ne4 { With a good position. } *

