[Black "3. d5 sidelines #4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. Nxd5 { This move is rather popular at a club level. } 5... Nxd5 { I think it's good for Black to exchange one pair of knights so that we won't have space problems. } 6. cxd5 d6 { The trade of knights has favoured Black. Now our dark-squared bishop will be more active on the a1-h8 diagonal than it usually is. } 7. e4 g6 { Now we can develop the bishop to g7. } 8. Nf3 Bg7 { Compared to a normal Benoni we have an improved position because of our stronger than usual bishop. } 9. Bd3 O-O ( { The immediate } 9... Bg4 { can be considered as well. } ) 10. O-O Bg4 { We're going to trade off our light-squared bishop soon. The knight then comes to d7. Black has a comfortable position. Note our good control over the e5-square and the active g7-bishop. } *

