1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. Nxd5 { This move is rather popular at a club level. } 5... Nxd5 { I think it's good for Black to exchange one pair of knights so that we won't have space problems. } 6. cxd5 d6 { The trade of knights has favoured Black. Now our dark-squared bishop will be more active on the a1-h8 diagonal than it usually is. } 7. Nf3 Be7 { A change of plans! The bishop will come to the long diagonal via f6. } ( { It makes more sense for White to develop the knight first. The idea is to meet } 7... g6 { with } 8. Bg5 { . } ) 8. e4 O-O { Black's ideas are ... Bg4 or ...f5. } 9. Bd3 Bg4 { A typical idea in the Benoni: trading the light-squared bishop for the knight. } 10. O-O Bf6 { Our bishop has reached the long diagonal anyway. On f6 it's just as good as on g7. } 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 Nd7 { Black has a nice position. He has good control over e5 and and an active bishop on the long diagonal. } *

