1. d4 Nf6 2. g4 { White plays an early gambit. It seems this move has many names, among them being the Bronstein Gambit and the Humphrey Bogart Gambit. GM Simon Williams who has also played 2. g4 called it the Kilkenny Gambit. Whatever its name, this doesn't seem like a sound gambit, but rather an attempt to confuse the opponent as soon as move 2. } 2... Nxg4 { I guess we have to accept the challenge. } 3. e4 d5 { I like this move because we immediately get a foothold in the centre. } 4. Be2 { This is White's idea. } 4... Qd7 { Let me suggest this move. According to my database it's a novelty. The point is that in case of e5 Black can play ...b6 and ...Ba6 in order to exchange the light-squared bishop, analogous to some lines in the French Defense. } 5. e5 h5 { Preparing the knight retreat to h6. } 6. Nf3 e6 { As explained before, our plan is to continue ...b6 and ...Ba6 in order to exchange light-squared bishops. } 7. Bd3 b6 8. Qe2 { Trying to prevent ...Ba6. } 8... a5 { This way we can nevertheless force their exchange. } 9. Nc3 Ba6 { Just according to plan. } 10. Bxa6 Nxa6 { White has some compensation for pawn, but little by little our extra pawn should tell. } *

